Explain to me what's BAD about this bill?  It still allows for "old-style" bankruptcy, but makes sure that those with REAL assets can't get out from under debts they just don't want to pay.  Heck, there was a 60-minutes story (or 20/20, one of those news shows) a few years back about somebody that went into bankruptcy in florida... with a 5000 sq ft mansion, multiple vehicles, etc.  Not exactly risking being in the poor house.  But this bill will also allow those with nothing to get out from under debt, just as they do today.
<br />

