I do not agree that you should base a future repayment plan on previous year's income-for the same reasons stated in the story.  Who is to say you will be ABLE to keep that job and keep paying that?
<br />

<br />
There should be a provision for changing categories (same judge who ordered repayment plan vice liquidation to avoid judge-shopping) in the event of loss of employment (not quitting, being fired).
