			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I personaly have filed Chapter 13 (when I was 20) I was in about 24k worth of dept. My truck got repo'd. I was working 2 jobs and going to school. First job was to pay insurance (health and auto) the other to make my car payment. The second job which I used to pay my car note with closed up (mom and pop video store). If this was at the begining of a semester I would have dropped all of my classes and got a full time job. But it was almost mid term and my last semester.
<br />

<br />
I was living at home but my parents couldn't help. Dad was working for a temp agency because the IT/IS job he had was outsourced to IBM GLobal services and he was waiting to get hired on full time with IBM (which happedned 2 weeks after I filed my 13 and almost tripled his income. Mom had been let go by her bank after 19 1/2 years becuase someone caught wind she was going to retire (her package was worth over 250k and she'd have gotten it in one lump sum) though the case wouln't hold water due to the 38 page bullshit firing evaluation she got.
<br />

<br />
My truck was co-signed by my grandfather. His credit was fucking bulletproff. I was sick, I couldn't let them go after him. While having hella credit... he was disabled living off of SS and disability. He had no assests and my grandmothers income just covered the rest of the living expenses. I HAD TO DO SOME THING QUICK!!
<br />

<br />
So I bit the bullet and filed chapter 13. I got the truck back the bank quit calling my grandfather and me and my wages were garnished. That summer I landed my first IT/IS job. I was making 4 times what I was at my other job. I stayed on the budget that I was on due to being bankrupt. In 18 months I saved the money and I wrote a check paying the bankruptcey off 3 yeas early.
<br />

<br />
I have been dept free accpet me buying a house since then. This June it leaves my credit report forever.
<br />

<br />
NO I do not advise anyone filing. I had to because I was not going to drag my grandparents and parent down with me.
<br />

<br />
So now maybe some of you can better understand why I have no sympathy for people who live off of the system. Who refuse to work 2 or 3 dead end jobs to make ends meet. Who wont go to school part time to get an education to better themselfs. Who fucking live paycheck to paycheck and off of goddamned credit cards.
<br />

<br />
As far as this bill goes....
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Ordering the most sweeping overhaul of U.S. bankruptcy laws in a quarter-century, the legislation would rework the centuries-old system — created soon after the Republic was founded — under which indebted people meet their obligations to creditors while also being able to get a fresh start. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
YES. Pay back what you owe or goddamnit more than pennies on the dollar. Companies lose money like this, in turn driving up prices to compensate for the loss. If Sears wants to cut you a deal on that 5k creditcard and asks you to pay 1500 that's their choice and should be put in the bankruptcy becase UNSECURED DEPT is nearly always erased.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Opponents say it would fall hard on low-income working people, single mothers, minorities and the elderly and would remove a safety net for those who have lost their jobs or face mounting medical bills. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Medical Bills aside please. If your ass is financing your fucking dinner at Jack in the Box on your America Depressed (I know what I called it) because you don't have the cash you are a fucking moron. I don't care if you have 12 kids at home that need food.. DON'T USE CREDIT CARDS!! if you have 5 bucks BUY RAMEN NOODLES!! Hell 2 bucks at some stores will buy you 12 packs of ramen. For gods sake its not great but you wont fucking starve to death. 
<br />

<br />
Credit Card and Car payments are the montra of the middle class. Credit Cards and Car payments are considered "Normal".. Fuck being normal be weird I'm called weird by all of my friends because I have a 3 bedroom 1200 square foot home in a nice part of town that sits on a quarter acre lot and my and my motrgage is less than 500 dollars a month. MOST in my part of town are in the 800-1100 range. I saved money eating beans and rice, rice and beans to make a hell of a down payment. While my friends were living it up in Jamaca, Buenos Aries and other areas of the world on credit cards. I was watching tv on a 13 inch black and white and playing EQ on a 400mhz P2 with 256 meg of ram and a 32meg pci voodoo video card. 
<br />

<br />
Now they have big cars and nice homes but can't do shit. I still live on a strick budget.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Those with insufficient assets or income could still file a Chapter 7 bankruptcy, which if approved by a judge erases debts entirely after certain assets are forfeited. But those with income above the state's median income who can pay at least $6,000 over five years — $100 a month — would be forced into Chapter 13, where a judge would then order a repayment plan. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
As it fucking should be. You can still get housing after a 7 IF and thats a big IF they take your home. Some states have a clause (all should IMHO) that allows you to keep your home. If they wanted to revise this clause force the person filing chapter 7 to sell the home and buy a smaller one. Court approved financing at a standard 12% apr untill the bankruptcy is finished.. or reduce the APR by .5% a year untill the bankruptcey is paid off (standard 5 years). This still leaves them at a higher than the average APR but it should... their credit is fucked... right? Then using the "Proffit" from the selling of their privious home to go twards dept. Thus forcing the 7 to a 13 so that some of the remaining balance can be paid back. Of couse this would be for home owners. Renters should recive a letter of notice to present to potencial land lords guaranteeing them payment else penalty added to the bankruptcy and wages further garnished (say minimum 75% of rent which would be paid to the land lord).
<br />

<br />
My opinions however extend only to the individual. Bussinesses need much much MUCH tigher restrictions when filing.
<br />

<br />
