				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Basically the idea was to get as short a term as you can afford, even if it means taking less of a dwelling, since you'll pay it off WAY faster, and have WAY more money in the end.
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
More or less.
<br />

<br />
I think in the 3 years I have lived in my house prior to the refinancing I paid 17,000 dollars in intrest alone. 17k on a 65k loan..... WTF.. 
<br />

<br />
This way (now) MORE of my monthy payment goes tward the principal of the loan. I had an Amortizaton of my loan. The acctual ammount of money going toward the principal of my loand was pitiful. NOW it's a much healthier chunk... this makes me happy.
<br />

<br />
OH... for those of you who are interested in learning more about the evils of creditcards and ways of getting out of dept without going bankrupt follow the link below. I wish I had found him before I filed.
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.daveramsey.com/" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://www.daveramsey.com/</a>
<br />

<br />
*note* he teaches this from a Christian veiwpoint so I'm sure some of you will damn him without ever giving him a chance. HOWEVER, his first priority when you ask him a question is NOT your faith but rather how serious you ar about getting out of dept and what you're willing to give up ( toys.... Homes, Cars, Trucks, Boats...) What shit in your life can you do without. 
<br />
He teaches from the heart and from experience. He wasn't always a Millionaire .... he's been one twice. The first time was on paper... he was a realistate investor.... and had millions on paper... and credit. He lost it all... Now he teaches people how to get out of dept and live a dept free lifestyle.
<br />

<br />
I can personaly say that following his teachings has changed my life. Do I do everythign he says? NO... Do I agree with what he says all the time? NO. But I can say that if you follow the basics of what his message is you WILL change your financial situation.
<br />

<br />
anywho... I'll get off my soapbox now.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
